    <summary>Provides data for the <see cref="E:Microsoft.Win32.SystemEvents.PowerModeChanged" /> event.</summary>
    <remarks>
      <format type="text/markdown"><![CDATA[  
  
## Remarks  
 A <xref:Microsoft.Win32.SystemEvents.PowerModeChanged> event is raised when the user suspends or resumes the operating system, or when a system power status notification occurs. A system power status notification can occur when a weak or charging power source is detected, or when a transition from AC or battery power source occurs.  
  
 The <xref:Microsoft.Win32.PowerModeChangedEventArgs.Mode%2A> property of a <xref:Microsoft.Win32.PowerModeChangedEventArgs> indicates the type of power mode event that has occurred.  
  
 ]]></format>
    </remarks>
